data.chText: 同意；准许；允许
data.enText: permission to do sth, especially given by sb in authority

data.chText: 16岁以下的儿童不得自行同意接受治疗。
data.enText: Children under 16 cannot give consent to medical treatment.

data.chText: 要求有家长的书面同意。
data.enText: The written consent of a parent is required.

data.chText: 拒不同意
data.enText: to refuse/withhold your consent

data.chText: 他因未征得车主的同意自行开走车而受到指控。
data.enText: He is charged with taking a car without the owner's consent .

data.chText: 同意；赞同
data.enText: agreement about sth

data.chText: 大家一致同意选她为领导人。
data.enText: She was chosen as leader by common consent (= everyone agreed to the choice) .

data.chText: 按照双方同意，他们没有约会。
data.enText: By mutual consent they didn't go out (= they both agreed not to) .

data.chText: 正式批准文件；批文
data.enText: an official document giving permission for sth

data.chText: 同意；准许；允许
data.enText: to agree to sth or give your permission for sth

data.chText: 她告诉他们她的打算时，他们欣然同意。
data.enText: When she told them what she intended they readily consented.

data.chText: 他勉强同意了女儿的婚事。
data.enText: He reluctantly consented to his daughter's marriage.

data.chText: 她最终同意回答我们的问题。
data.enText: She finally consented to answer our questions.

data.chText: 以上各词均含答应、同意之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to say that you will do what sb wants or that you will allow sth to happen.
agree

data.chText: 指答应、容许：
data.enText: to say that you will do what sb wants or that you will allow sth to happen

data.chText: 他同意让我早走。
data.enText: He agreed to let me go early.
approve

data.chText: 指批准、正式通过（计划、建议或要求）：
data.enText: to officially agree to a plan, suggestion or request

data.chText: 委员会一致通过了计划。
data.enText: The committee unanimously approved the plan.
consent

data.chText: 指同意、准许、允许：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to agree to sth or give your permission for sth

data.chText: 她最终同意回答我们的问题。
data.enText: She finally consented to answer our questions.
acquiesce

data.chText: 指默然接受、默认、默许、顺从：
data.enText: ( formal ) to accept sth without arguing, even if you do not really agree with it

data.chText: 政府高级官员必然已经默许掩盖真相。
data.enText: Senior government figures must have acquiesced in the cover-up.
to agree/consent to sth
to agree/consent to do sth
to be prepared/willing/unwilling/forced to agree/approve/consent/acquiesce
to refuse to agree/approve/consent/acquiesce
to agree to/approve/consent to a request
to agree to a demand
to readily agree to/approve/consent to/acquiesce in sth
to reluctantly agree to/approve/consent to/acquiesce in sth

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + sent 感觉 → 同感 → 同意

ex.enText: The firm agreed to the terms.

ex.chText: 那名导演同意拍那部电影。
ex.enText: That director agreed to do the film.

ex.chText: 如今大多数人这么认为，能力比学历更重要。
ex.enText: Most people nowadays would agree that ability is more important than a diploma.

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，指就某一计划、安排、建议等与他人持相同看法，常后接介词 to/with、动词不定式或 that 从句。

ex.enText: He didn't accede to my request.

ex.chText: 我们大家都同意要他辞职的请求。
ex.enText: We all acceded to the demands for his resignation.

synonyms.bx: 尤指最初不同意后又应允要求、请求、计划等，常后接介词 to。

ex.enText: I strongly approve of your proposal.

ex.chText: 玛丽想当然地认为他们一定会同意这个想法。
ex.enText: Mary took it for granted that they would approve of the idea.

synonyms.bx: 指认为某人或某事是好的、对的、合适的，常后接介词 of。

ex.enText: He assented to the committee's proposal.

ex.chText: 他们同意合同的条款了吗？
ex.enText: Have they assented to the terms of the contract?

synonyms.bx: 指审慎考虑后同意某项建议、要求、意见、计划等，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我确信你的老师不会同意的。
ex.enText: I'm sure your teacher won't consent.

ex.chText: 经过几个小时的劝说，他们同意放弃罢工。
ex.enText: After hours of persuasion they consented to abandon the strike.

ex.chText: 她父亲勉强答应了这桩婚姻。
ex.enText: Her father reluctantly consented to the marriage.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，指同意别人的请求、建议或满足他人的愿望，常后接介词 to 或带 to 的动词不定式。

value.def: If you give your consent to something, you give someone permission to do it.

example.ex: At approximately 11:30 p.m., Pollard finally gave his consent to the search...
example.tran: 大概晚上11点半的时候，波拉德最终同意进行搜查。

example.ex: Can my child be medically examined without my consent?
example.tran: 能不经我的同意就对我的孩子进行体检吗？

value.def: If you consent to something, you agree to do it or to allow it to be done.

example.ex: He asked Ginny if she would consent to a small celebration after the christening...
example.tran: 他问金尼是否同意在洗礼之后小小地庆祝一下。

example.ex: I was a little surprised when she consented.
example.tran: 我有点儿吃惊她竟然同意了。

value.def: If something happens by common consent or by mutual consent, it happens as the result of an agreement between the people or groups involved.

example.ex: By common consent their talk avoided the reason for their being there at all...
example.tran: 双方达成共识，他们的谈话对他们去那儿的原因完全避而不谈。

example.ex: He left the company by mutual consent last September.
example.tran: 去年9月，经双方同意，他离开了公司。

value.tran: 经一致同意;经双方同意

value.def: You can use by general consent or by common consent to indicate that most people agree that something is true.

example.ex: By common consent this election constituted a historic step on the road to democracy.
example.tran: 普遍认为这次选举是迈上民主之路的历史性一步。
